            "anno_id": 1,
            "text": " $ Indeed, Let  $t_0 < t_1 < t_2$ , and let  $\\lambda \\in (0,1)$ . Let  $x \\in (1-\\lambda)W_{t_1} + \\lambda W_{t_2}$ , and let  $u \\in \\Omega$ . Let  $x_i \\in W_{t_i}, i = 1, 2$ , such that  $x = (1 - \\lambda)x_1 + \\lambda x_2$ . Denote  $t_{\\lambda} := (1 - \\lambda)t_1 + \\lambda t_2$ . Then",
            "line_with_spans": [
